    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AC/8–851: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic and Consular Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d457fn1">Drafted by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WJA1"
                            >Waldo</persName>; cleared by <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>;
                        authorized for transmission and signed for the Secretary by Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_JGL1">G. L. Jones</persName>. Sent to Amman, Tel Aviv,
                        Jerusalem, Beirut, Damascus, Jidda, Baghdad, and Cairo. Repeated for
                        information to London, Paris (for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_PEE1"
                            >Palmer</persName>), and Ankara.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-08T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Shld you be queried concerning unfortunate press reports from <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> sources Jlem to effect US is preparing “vast
                    scheme aimed at solution Palestine problem” you may say that these reports
                    completely erroneous. Fact is US in line its obligations as member <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> has instr
                    its rep <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> to suggest more authoritative and
                    direct role on part of <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> than heretofore
                    assumed re solution Palestine question (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss>s Jslm 137 June 12 <gloss target="#t_Unpal1">Unpal</gloss>
                        270<note n="2" xml:id="d457fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_714">p. 714</ref>.</note> and
                    7 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] Jul 7 <gloss target="#t_Unpal1">Unpal</gloss>
                        276).<note n="3" xml:id="d457fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_753">p. 753</ref>.</note> It
                    understood <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> presently considering
                    possibilities such new approach in Paris. Any proposals to parties, however,
                    will be responsibility of <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> and will have been
                    worked out by that <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> org.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> as result query Israel Emb Wash re press
                    reports, Dept explained foregoing to Israel Emb Rep. Expressed hope Israel wld
                    accept any invitation extended without requiring submission detailed agenda
                    beforehand. Said solution smallest aspect Palestine problem wld be constructive
                    step forward and hoped Israel wld forego past insistence on “orthodox
                    approach”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
